HEADWORD: Highflier
<hw>High"fli`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who is extravagant in pretensions, opinions, or manners; one who is
highfaluting.</def> <rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a person of great ability and ambition.</def>
<wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
